{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17629528","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17629528"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T17:07:16+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T17:07:16+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17288"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17288","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17288"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.05,0.29,0.48,0.14,0.05]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9978"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78766"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9978","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9978"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17288"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64115"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4899"},{"type":"tags","id":"4901"},{"type":"tags","id":"4930"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"7166"},{"type":"tags","id":"7213"},{"type":"tags","id":"7227"},{"type":"tags","id":"7322"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"23372"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23374"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78766","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/78766"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following nerve root levels is associated with the supraclavicular nerves of the cervical plexus?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["C2 only","C2,3","C3,4","C1-3","C3 only"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe supraclavicular nerves are branches of the cervical plexus, which is formed by the anterior rami of the first four cervical spinal nerves (C1-C4). These nerves specifically arise from the \u003Cstrong\u003EC3,4\u003C/strong\u003E nerve roots. They provide sensory innervation to the skin over the shoulder and upper chest.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EC2 only\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect as the supraclavicular nerves do not arise from this level alone. The C2 nerve root contributes to other branches of the cervical plexus, such as the lesser occipital nerve.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EC2,3\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect because, while these levels contribute to the cervical plexus, the supraclavicular nerves specifically arise from C3 and C4.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EC1-3\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect as the supraclavicular nerves do not involve the C1 nerve root. The C1 nerve root primarily contributes to the ansa cervicalis and other motor branches.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EC3 only\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect because the supraclavicular nerves arise from both C3 and C4, not C3 alone.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The supraclavicular nerves arise from the cervical plexus, specifically from the C3 and C4 nerve roots.","The cervical plexus is a network of nerves formed by the anterior rami of the first four cervical spinal nerves (C1-C4).","The supraclavicular nerves provide sensory innervation to the skin over the shoulder and upper chest."],"references":[]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64115"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17288"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64115","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/64115"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-12T16:46:13+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-12T16:4